\begin_layout Part
Overview
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The denuder-based trace gas sampler or 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

denuder-REA system
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 helps researchers accomplish measurements of trace gas fluxes with traditional
 wet-chemical analyses.
 The predominant technique for measuring trace gas fluxes, eddy covariance
 (EC), depends on cospatial, cotemporal, high-frequency (â‰¥10Hz) measurements
 of both vertical wind speed and gas concentration.
 The denuder-REA system avoids such constraints by employing the relaxed
 eddy accumulation (REA) technique instead.
 Glass honeycomb denuders facilitate the measurement of reactive species
 by allowing for adsorptive coatings targeting the gas species of interest.
\end_layout

