\begin_layout Paragraph
Standalone deployment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a typical deployment, the denuder-REA system is setup in a self-contained
 fashion.
 It may be in the vincinity of additional sampling systems but there is
 no direct collaboration with those systems.
 That is, data collected by the denuder-REA is not available to other systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Co-deploy with gradient sampler
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The denuder-REA can also be deployed in conjunction with a gradient sampler
 system.
 In this arrangement, the denuder-REA acts as the controlling datalogger
 and the gradient sampler datalogger passively listens to data output by
 the sonic anemometer and infrared gas analyzer.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The combination anemometer/IRGA (EC150) cannot be used for co-deployment
 because it does not provide a secondary data output to provide the gradient
 sampler datalogger.
 The Campbell Scientific CSAT3 and LI-COR Biosciences LI7500 must be used
 instead because they both can simultaneously output data via SDM (Campbellsci
 proprietary) and serial (RS-232) protocols.
\end_layout

